---
import ServicePage from '../layouts/ServicePage.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<ServicePage
  title="On-Page SEO Services UK | MM SEO"
  description="On-page SEO from an experienced freelance consultant. Based in Stockport, serving clients across the UK."
  canonical="https://www.mmseo.co.uk/on-page-seo/"
  breadcrumb="On-Page SEO"
>

  <!-- ── 1. Hero band (dark) ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-hero section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-hero-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">On-Page SEO | Manchester &amp; UK</p>
      <h1 class="sp-h1">On-Page SEO: Making Every Page Work Harder</h1>
      <p class="sp-intro">
        Rankings come from Google understanding exactly what a page is about and
        trusting that it's the best answer for the searcher. On-page SEO is the
        discipline of making that case as clearly and compellingly as possible,
        through structure, content, and signals that are entirely within your control.
      </p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">Book a Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 2. Main content (light) ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-content section-light">
    <div class="container sp-content-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2">What On-Page SEO Covers</h2>

      <p>
        On-page SEO is the layer of optimisation that sits between your technical
        foundations and your off-page authority. It ensures that each page on your
        site is structured to rank and to convert once people arrive.
      </p>
      <p>
        I approach on-page work page by page, starting with your highest-priority
        commercial pages and working outward. Every change I recommend has a clear
        rationale tied to either ranking performance or user experience, usually both.
      </p>
      <p>
        Common mistakes I fix include pages targeting the wrong keyword entirely,
        H1 tags that don't match search intent, over-optimised content that reads
        like it was written for a bot, and internal links that bleed authority away
        from your most important pages.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3">On-page elements I optimise</h3>
      <ul class="sp-list">
        <li><strong>Title tags</strong>: precise keyword placement, search intent alignment, click-through rate optimisation</li>
        <li><strong>Meta descriptions</strong>: compelling copy that improves CTR from SERPs, even though it's not a ranking factor</li>
        <li><strong>H-tag hierarchy</strong>: H1, H2, H3 structure that signals topic relevance without keyword stuffing</li>
        <li><strong>Content optimisation</strong>: NLP-informed rewrites, semantic coverage, entity inclusion, readability</li>
        <li><strong>Internal linking</strong>: strategic links that distribute authority, aid crawling, and guide users deeper</li>
        <li><strong>Image optimisation</strong>: descriptive alt text, file naming, WebP/AVIF formats, dimensions for CLS</li>
        <li><strong>Schema markup</strong>: structured data to enhance SERP appearance (FAQ, HowTo, Product, Review)</li>
        <li><strong>URL structure</strong>: clean, descriptive URLs that reinforce keyword targeting</li>
        <li><strong>Content freshness</strong>: identifying pages where updating or expanding content will recover lost rankings</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 3. Why it matters (dark) ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-why section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-why-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2 chalk">Intent Alignment: The Detail Most Get Wrong</h2>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        The single most important principle in on-page SEO is intent alignment.
        Google doesn't just match keywords; it matches intent. If someone searches
        "best accounting software for small business" they want a comparison guide,
        not a product page. If they search "buy accounting software" they want to
        convert. Sending the wrong page type to the wrong query is one of the most
        common reasons pages fail to rank.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        I audit every priority page against its target keyword's dominant intent,
        informational, commercial, or transactional, and ensure the page type,
        content depth, and structure all match what Google's top results show us
        is working. It's a more rigorous approach than most agencies apply, and it
        produces measurably better outcomes.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        On-page optimisation also directly supports conversion. Pages that are
        clear, well-structured, and trust-building convert at higher rates. Every
        on-page recommendation I make is made with both the crawler and the human
        visitor in mind.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 4. Relevant result (light) ──────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-result section-light">
    <div class="container sp-result-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow dark-eyebrow">Proven Results</p>
      <blockquote class="sp-quote">
        <p class="sp-quote-metric">75+ Page 1 rankings · +552% organic revenue</p>
        <p class="sp-quote-context">
          For Illuminated Mirrors, a complete content rewrite aligned to search intent,
          combined with a structural overhaul of their product and category pages,
          delivered 75+ page one rankings and contributed directly to 552% organic
          revenue growth within six months.
        </p>
        <footer class="sp-quote-credit">— Illuminated Mirrors (eCommerce · UK)</footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 5. Contact CTA ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <ContactForm />

</ServicePage>

<style>
  .section-dark  { background-color: var(--ink);  color: var(--chalk); }
  .section-light { background-color: var(--chalk); color: var(--ink); }

  .container {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 2rem);
  }

  .sp-hero { padding: 5rem 0 4rem; }
  .sp-hero-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .dark-eyebrow { color: var(--accent); }

  .sp-h1 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--chalk);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sp-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background-color: var(--accent-dk); }

  .sp-content { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-content-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .sp-h2 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-h2.chalk { color: var(--chalk); }

  .sp-h3 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .sp-content p, .sp-content-inner p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }

  .sp-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sp-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }
  .sp-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .sp-why { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-why-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .chalk { color: var(--chalk); }
  .chalk-muted {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
  }

  .sp-result { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-result-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .sp-quote {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background-color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.04);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sp-quote-metric {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-quote-context {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.75);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-quote-credit {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .reveal {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(24px);
    transition: opacity 0.55s ease, transform 0.55s ease;
  }
  .reveal.visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: none;
  }
</style>

<script>
  const revealEls = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); io.unobserve(e.target); } }),
    { threshold: 0.12 }
  );
  revealEls.forEach(el => io.observe(el));
</script>
